menu "Storage Eviction"

    config STORAGE_EVICTION_TARGET_MIB
        int "Free space trigger threshold in MiB"
        default 1024
        help
            Low watermark for the SD card free space. When free space
            falls below this threshold, an eviction pass starts and
            keeps deleting until free space reaches the high watermark
            (target + headroom). See STORAGE_EVICTION_HEADROOM_MIB.

    config STORAGE_EVICTION_HEADROOM_MIB
        int "Free space headroom in MiB above target"
        default 4096
        help
            Hysteresis between the trigger threshold and the stop
            condition. Once eviction starts (free < target), it keeps
            running until free >= target + headroom. A larger headroom
            means fewer eviction passes but each pass deletes more
            files; a value of 0 reverts to single-watermark behavior
            and risks thrashing across the target line.

    config STORAGE_EVICTION_INITIAL_AGE_DAYS
        int "Initial age threshold in days"
        default 30
        help
            First eviction pass deletes files not accessed within
            this many days. If more space is needed, the threshold
            is halved on each subsequent pass.

    config STORAGE_EVICTION_MIN_AGE_HOURS
        int "Minimum age threshold in hours"
        default 4
        help
            Floor for the age threshold. Files accessed more recently
            than this are never deleted, even if the free space target
            has not been reached.

    config CHANNEL_EVICTION_AGE_DAYS
        int "Channel cache eviction age in days"
        default 60
        help
            Channel cache files (.cache, .json, .settings.json) that
            have not been loaded for playback within this many days
            are deleted. Channels in the active playset are always
            protected regardless of age.

endmenu
